The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Three killed in road mishaps
                                                                                                               Three killed in road mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Three pedestrians died in three mishaps in the city on Tuesday.        
	Around 8am, an unidentified man in his early-30s sustained head injuries after being hit by a minibus while trying to cross Narkeldanga Main Road. He was declared dead at RG Kar Medical College and Hospital.        
	Around 2pm, a pilgrim from Uttar Pradesh was crushed under the wheels of a south-bound minibus on Strand Road, near Prinsep Ghat. Cops said Ram Dulal Biswakarma, 70, who had gone to the area for a dip in the Hooghly, was declared dead at SSKM Hospital.        
	Both drivers fled leaving their buses behind.        
	Around 11am, 36-year-old Baneswar Shau, a resident of Kaikhali, died after being knocked down by a car on VIP Road, near the Rajarhat flyover.         
	Residents rushed Shau to a nearby nursing home, where he was declared dead.        
	Local people stopped the driver, Manish Gupta, and handed him over to us. We arrested him and seized the vehicle, said a senior officer of Baguiati police station.                                                                                                                                                                           
